{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\n\nAn assessment of rebar's config surface (`src/rebar/_config_schema.py` vs this\nproject's `rebar.toml`) identified settled rollout flags and retired alternatives to\nprune, one settled feature to activate by dogfooding, and an authenticated-identity\nrollout to stand up. Each decision is backed by a code-level investigation recorded on\nthe relevant child. This epic delivers all of it plus a doc-accuracy sweep.\n\n## Workstreams\n\n- **Prune (removal approved):** `reconciler.baseline_dual_write` +\n  `baseline_consumer_swap` (→ always-on); the three settled verify defaults\n  `progressive_drift_refresh` / `remediation_mode` / `novelty_drop_active` (→ always-on);\n  `verify.require_signature_for_close` (retired alternative); and\n  `compact.emit_legacy_signature_mirror` (a one-way door — landed behind a readiness-gate\n  check).\n- **Activate by dogfooding:** `verify.completion_floor_active` — assessed as fully\n  implemented AND already calibrated (gold-set 30/30, κ=1.0, zero must-never-suppress\n  anchors dropped; docs/calibration/completion_floor.md). Enable it in THIS project.\n- **Authenticated-identity rollout:** stand up signing identity for every ticket-event\n  writer (local dev; AWS review-bot + auto-lander; GitHub Actions reconciler + canary),\n  secrets handled securely, AWS/GitHub using the shared Rebar Bot identity. The actual\n  `require_authenticated` flag flip is OUT OF SCOPE here (setup only).\n- **Doc-accuracy sweep** for every removed key + overall config-doc correctness.\n\n## KEEP (assessed, not touched)\n\nNothing on the original KEEP list survives as keep: the signature-mirror is now a\nremoval (readiness-gated) and the completion floor is now an activation. There are no\nremaining keep-dormant decisions in this epic's scope.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- The four approved removals are gone from the schema, their behavior hardcoded, no dead\n  back-out code remains, and no doc/help/release-note references a removed key.\n- `completion_floor_active` is enabled in this project's `rebar.toml` with the sidecar\n  drop-audit surface identified for monitoring.\n- Every ticket-event-writing environment can sign as its intended identity (bot for\n  AWS/GitHub); the reconciler code path is fixed to route through the signing seam; the\n  test suite has a defensive guard so a stray global enforcement env can't red the build.\n- `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass on the landed result.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] All child stories are closed.\n- [ ] `rebar` runs clean against this project's `rebar.toml` (no `unknown key … ignored` warnings; removed keys deleted from `rebar.toml`).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` pass on the landed result.\n- [ ] A repo-wide grep confirms no committed doc/help/release-note references any removed config key."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783968862737053001,"uuid":"f01cc0af-6786-44d7-9d83-0abb829d0f75"}